`crates/` contains a single crate, `steno`, with no other members. There's no workspace-level intent.md, so this rollup has nothing of its own to add beyond what `steno/rollup.ctx` already states in full: it's a `.steno`-dictionary compiler exposing `expand_dict`, dictionary builders, and snippet builders, backed by a strict parse→expand→render pipeline and a corpus-driven test suite tied to the root `dict.steno`.

Any cross-file work in this tree starts and ends inside `steno/` — there is no sibling crate to coordinate with, no shared build tooling here, and no workspace-wide invariant beyond what's already documented at the crate level.

intent_divergence: no intent.md exists at the `crates` level (or at the crate root), so no divergence can be assessed.